# ▶️ SECTION 5: How JavaScript Runs

---

# Browser Environment

Browser includes:

### JS Engine

Examples:

* Chrome → V8
* Firefox → SpiderMonkey
* Safari → JavaScriptCore

---

# Execution Flow:

```txt id="4blv6x"
Code → Parse → Compile/JIT → Execute
```

---

# 🧠 JS Engine Components:

---

## Parser

Reads code

---

## AST (Abstract Syntax Tree)

Code structure representation

---

## Interpreter

Executes quickly

---

## Compiler (JIT)

Optimizes hot code

---

# ⚡ Modern JS:

Not purely interpreted.

### It uses:

# Just-In-Time Compilation

